ved_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"parents":[{"sha":"82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/commits/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","html_url":"https://github.com/honojs/hono/commit/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06"}]},{"sha":"82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","node_id":"C_kwDOGiE5WNoAKDgyZGFkNjI5N2M5MGMzM2M0MWJmNDhiNDUzMDUwOWEyMTU4OGFkMDY","commit":{"author":{"name":"francisjohnjohnston-web","email":"francisjohnjohnston@gmail.com","date":"2026-05-24T08:42:00Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-24T08:42:00Z"},"message":"fix(serve-static): normalize all backslashes in file paths, not just the first (#4962)\n\n`getFilePathWithoutDefaultDocument` converts backslash separators to slashes so\nthe same path resolves consistently regardless of the separator style of the\nincoming request. The replace used a non-global regex (`/\\/`), so only the\nFIRST backslash was converted: a path with multiple segments like\n`foo\\bar\\baz.txt` became `foo/bar\\baz.txt` — mixed separators that resolve to the\nwrong file (or 404) on platforms that don't treat `\\` as a separator. The\nadjacent comment (`foo\\bar.txt => foo/bar.txt`) shows the intent was to\nnormalize all of them.\n\nFix: add the `g` flag (`/\\/g`). Behaviour is unchanged for any path with zero\nor one backslash, so all existing tests pass; added a regression test covering a\nmulti-segment path (with and without `root`) that returns the broken\n`foo/bar\\baz.txt` before this change.\n\ntsc --noEmit clean; eslint + prettier clean.\n\nCo-authored-by: Prodia Evolution Worker <evo@prodia.dev>","tree":{"sha":"7ebd093577e3075a8a148bbff99fc2b65b3f0169","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/git/trees/7ebd093577e3075a8a148bbff99fc2b65b3f0169"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/git/commits/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqErnYCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAAq+4QADxI7LKb+f2wV3IizYddQMFi\nviaSPMapOKvvLOGmoP8jaVcoSnty95tURKVKCr2Lyk9+378zDACoFoG0cSo4MhU1\nbMYsHxoutNOtot93DJfCEMKsS3sQweDOkuBtqVp3cnldSgXMa2PxjB3WxRceKHEJ\nO0/bq9fXkhacUBbtiTzoW7qDDuS/xTquKxc8XFKOBfKQQNRh2lIYmQQufMxzKyzb\nbSmx+hD6XSVwgJ8sJ4Fs3cd4Cdb/GiFrkt+JyYLn3xPAgJzrwlRhRxTJRkcK3DlO\n+48s4HWZpXehg2NgLGT6lhen8JeVb/Hx27eWzbHT3Xf7GBXdaeet6GTEqwoCN6W3\nn1UZocoLUjk41UW8WN/8pEIjI3IklXB0VDeT4i7aoIAuNVMIfzErdyzbSqhjdF6D\nyMo3TfNQNXqg1Q5bW2HDKpcQU+/xJJft0VhFmegPDgXqilNvrb9jM82jsv4HmOKS\nVTWk01pGOXDf259iE9bg6bVO4MiC83I3W3zdq25a/sQqR6CEgG2ncHoVWiC/EfQT\nLt26nwbays4vpcwQc1YdvvC63W4ko5HuMnF4iA+p8TVpsf+V8KOytIEU1k5kwKzy\n8kSwrtB2bfVHcYQQ24dJmfVbegsYpEAz+MvxFiihNX5RnFFRV+kf3RP8iPbLCw0V\nW3ENoi0r4svLh4dy5iy+\n=CV8f\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 7ebd093577e3075a8a148bbff99fc2b65b3f0169\nparent 2f01b774b168911d24e4864fb66054f5de9d9a4e\nauthor francisjohnjohnston-web <francisjohnjohnston@gmail.com> 1779612120 +0100\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779612120 +0900\n\nfix(serve-static): normalize all backslashes in file paths, not just the first (#4962)\n\n`getFilePathWithoutDefaultDocument` converts backslash separators to slashes so\nthe same path resolves consistently regardless of the separator style of the\nincoming request. The replace used a non-global regex (`/\\/`), so only the\nFIRST backslash was converted: a path with multiple segments like\n`foo\\bar\\baz.txt` became `foo/bar\\baz.txt` — mixed separators that resolve to the\nwrong file (or 404) on platforms that don't treat `\\` as a separator. The\nadjacent comment (`foo\\bar.txt => foo/bar.txt`) shows the intent was to\nnormalize all of them.\n\nFix: add the `g` flag (`/\\/g`). Behaviour is unchanged for any path with zero\nor one backslash, so all existing tests pass; added a regression test covering a\nmulti-segment path (with and without `root`) that returns the broken\n`foo/bar\\baz.txt` before this change.\n\ntsc --noEmit clean; eslint + prettier clean.\n\nCo-authored-by: Prodia Evolution Worker <evo@prodia.dev>","verified_at":"2026-05-24T08:42:01Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/commits/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","html_url":"https://github.com/honojs/hono/commit/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/commits/82dad6297c90c33c41bf48b4530509a21588ad06/comments","author":{"login":"francisjohnjohnston-web","id":261208024,"node_id":"U_kgDOD5G32A","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/261208024?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web","html_url":"https://github.com/francisjohnjohnston-web","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/francisjohnjohnston-web/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"committer":{"login":"web-flow","id":19864447,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5ODY0NDQ3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19864447?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow","html_url":"https://github.com/web-flow","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-flow/followers","fol