tps://github.com/honojs/hono/commit/f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6"}]},{"sha":"f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6","node_id":"C_kwDOGiE5WNoAKGYwZWQyNDY1OTEzZjJhODllYmRmNjVjYzU0ZDYyNTQ5MTVmYzNmZjY","commit":{"author":{"name":"Shaurya Singh","email":"sshaurya914@gmail.com","date":"2026-05-22T09:05:23Z"},"committer":{"name":"GitHub","email":"noreply@github.com","date":"2026-05-22T09:05:23Z"},"message":"fix(compress): respect Accept-Encoding when encoding option is set (#4951)\n\n* fix(compress): skip compression when client does not accept the configured encoding\n\nWhen the encoding option is set, the middleware previously compressed responses\nunconditionally, regardless of the Accept-Encoding header. This could send a\nresponse in an encoding the client cannot decode (for example, returning gzip\nwhen the client only advertised deflate, or when Accept-Encoding is absent).\n\nHonor the client's Accept-Encoding header even when an encoding is explicitly\nconfigured, falling back to no compression when the configured encoding is\nnot accepted.\n\n* fix(compress): use parseAccept to honor q-values, wildcard, and case\n\nAddress review from @yusukebe. The previous version used String.includes\non the raw Accept-Encoding header, which treated x-gzip as gzip, ignored\nq=0 explicit refusals, and did not understand the wildcard. Switch to\nparseAccept (already used by accepts middleware) and pick the candidate\nencoding with the highest non-zero q value, falling back to the wildcard\nq if the candidate has no explicit entry.\n\nAdd seven regression tests covering q=0 on the configured encoding, q=0\nfallback to another candidate, wildcard \\*, case-insensitive tokens,\nx-gzip non-matching, highest-q wins, and gzip-over-deflate tie-break.\n\n* fix(compress): short-circuit selectEncoding when q is 1\n\nPer @usualoma: q values are almost always 1 in practice, so short-circuit\nand return immediately for the common path instead of continuing to scan\nthe remaining candidates.\n\n\nCo-authored-by: Yusuke Wada <yusuke@kamawada.com>\nCo-authored-by: Taku Amano <taku@taaas.jp>","tree":{"sha":"38a2598a3f5f6fbe0ac89c99f103f6dce5aaa4a0","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/git/trees/38a2598a3f5f6fbe0ac89c99f103f6dce5aaa4a0"},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/git/commits/f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6","comment_count":0,"verification":{"verified":true,"reason":"valid","signature":"-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsFcBAABCAAQBQJqEBxTCRC1aQ7uu5UhlAAApVMQAHGUDIiJJhlWA/KlfvmkRNUx\nsfTUj+qIvRqYpc870BHWUp4dgfO/fZtrUetbCyem2rkL54PJErf3TgNeFl0OzEK+\nERbtcSSGEWRnjtmF86LCvQr+Jw3Uzy5gNvuA0dHma7/PBt2Bpe/DtBnyxTA7zlZ0\n5954wx+1sabZj4kc6o6LOzye7NIe2mqsqcqDEb8gV5ffyDNDA03ytk+oowY2uvgh\nWs+0rsT3NPrHUqxF//M9sUceyU80azbUUjJgkZa66ylvF9cSsgdroyDuqaqiWkH8\nmRrIbzg+Hk7YlXqZwV7sgqP1OTHfz6gFhked+9F1bSeWmlKgj98LLtdXyvKZ4/7x\nrnjb7ueoOEdFiGenjlbb3eEfevZNNdGi8zpGIlTG+vZ8aSAtXpFLvbYH+CzP86SK\nGDI5Ll3xHZjSzNk79F3tLznXlOibWUDYmI42qGy+GR3ZAyfHdS0soNRfcfla7E7t\nyHIpGRT9tcJmtTgZMMv7zpsdbefdNut/jDnlpYYZ6YHygqM9iPif66hbcYsCjA1z\nJBplh8zGBof/V+QPdPDCTanxAkIZfQVicRbWfXr1UTRy+NdZpdLzkfRYsRT+lj4e\nYi2EyumJbk2J9sYYPb6/uvO87BS19fjynQ8VCiVVWiKeANpnbI5AxHW0CNT3gwea\nTJ4531Mc7AY43qDR7eFa\n=1MG4\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n","payload":"tree 38a2598a3f5f6fbe0ac89c99f103f6dce5aaa4a0\nparent a192df0844724aeaf5cbc6f1ea2f8425d3f8a86a\nauthor Shaurya Singh <sshaurya914@gmail.com> 1779440723 -0700\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1779440723 +0900\n\nfix(compress): respect Accept-Encoding when encoding option is set (#4951)\n\n* fix(compress): skip compression when client does not accept the configured encoding\n\nWhen the encoding option is set, the middleware previously compressed responses\nunconditionally, regardless of the Accept-Encoding header. This could send a\nresponse in an encoding the client cannot decode (for example, returning gzip\nwhen the client only advertised deflate, or when Accept-Encoding is absent).\n\nHonor the client's Accept-Encoding header even when an encoding is explicitly\nconfigured, falling back to no compression when the configured encoding is\nnot accepted.\n\n* fix(compress): use parseAccept to honor q-values, wildcard, and case\n\nAddress review from @yusukebe. The previous version used String.includes\non the raw Accept-Encoding header, which treated x-gzip as gzip, ignored\nq=0 explicit refusals, and did not understand the wildcard. Switch to\nparseAccept (already used by accepts middleware) and pick the candidate\nencoding with the highest non-zero q value, falling back to the wildcard\nq if the candidate has no explicit entry.\n\nAdd seven regression tests covering q=0 on the configured encoding, q=0\nfallback to another candidate, wildcard \\*, case-insensitive tokens,\nx-gzip non-matching, highest-q wins, and gzip-over-deflate tie-break.\n\n* fix(compress): short-circuit selectEncoding when q is 1\n\nPer @usualoma: q values are almost always 1 in practice, so short-circuit\nand return immediately for the common path instead of continuing to scan\nthe remaining candidates.\n\n\nCo-authored-by: Yusuke Wada <yusuke@kamawada.com>\nCo-authored-by: Taku Amano <taku@taaas.jp>","verified_at":"2026-05-22T09:05:24Z"}},"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/commits/f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6","html_url":"https://github.com/honojs/hono/commit/f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/honojs/hono/commits/f0ed2465913f2a89ebdf65cc54d6254915fc3ff6/comments","author":{"login":"LeSingh1","id":197028264,"node_id":"U_kgDOC75pqA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/197028264?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/LeSingh1","html_url":"https://github.com/LeSingh1","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LeSingh1/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LeSingh1/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LeSingh1/gists{/gist_id}","sta